\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Over the last few years there have been several major attacks on TLS 
\begin_inset Flex EntityXRef
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
RFC5246
\end_layout

\end_inset

, including attacks on its most commonly used ciphers and modes of operation.
 Details are given in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Attacks"

\end_inset

, but suffice it to say that both AES-CBC and RC4, which together make up
 for most current usage, have been seriously attacked in the context of
 TLS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This situation motivated the creation of the UTA working group, which is
 tasked with the creation of generic and protocol-specific recommendation
 for the use of TLS and DTLS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Attacks always get better; they never get worse
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 (ironically, this saying is attributed to the NSA).
 This list of attacks describes our knowledge as of this writing.
 It seems likely that new attacks will be invented in the future.
\end_layout

